Section.Catchline: Records concerning applicant; extent of confidentiality.

Subsection.Text: Test material is made confidential by s. 119.071(1)(a). An applicant may waive in writing the confidentiality of his or her examination answer sheet for the purpose of discussion with the State Fire Marshal or his or her staff.
All examination test questions, answer sheets, and grades shall be retained for a period of 2 years following the date of the examination.
